The paper deals with the problem of physical layer security in mmWave MIMO systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of hybrid precoding and combining transceiver architecture is a common technique in mmWave MIMO systems, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of artificial noise for jamming eavesdropper's reception, which is a signal processing technique (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes algorithms for secure transmission, which involves system design and optimization (cs.SY).
